parameters:
\N<Irime>I understand how you feel, and I want to help somehow, but I
have a match to prepare for tomorrow myself.

\N<Segi>It's okay, I can feel your concern, Irime-san. Besides...
there's no need for you to take time out for someone else's
sake.

\N<Segi>Let's both do our best and overcome this. I'll keep
striving, supported by the words you once said to me.
\N<Segi>That... I'll show them the pride of a woman.

\N<Hojiko's Wife>Ahaha, sorry about that? I said too much before the fight.
And I've been wanting to apologize to you.

\N<Hojiko's Wife>Yeah, I didn't see today's fight, but I can imagine what
happened.

\N<Hojiko's Wife>Knowing you, you let my husband win, didn't you? Just like I
asked.

\N<Hojiko's Wife>But, well... it was surprising. I never thought you'd make
eyes at my husband.

\N<Hojiko's Wife>You have such an innocent face, yet you're quite the vixen.
Poor Yuia must feel so sorry.

\N<Hojiko's Wife>You have such an innocent face, yet you're quite the vixen.
Poor Yuia must feel so sorry.
\N<Hojiko's Wife>Exactly what I said. A wife that's a nymphomaniac.

\N<Segi>Please correct yourself. I haven't been making eyes at Mr.
Hojiko...

\N<Hojiko's Wife>Oh scary, seeing that defiant attitude, did you already find
a new patron in Ryuda or something?

\N<Hojiko's Wife>Looks like I better make a quick exit. 'Touch not the cat
but a glove' and all that, ahaha.

\N<Ryuda Soldier>During the training session, the movement of you residents
is restricted. Therefore, we cannot allow anyone without
permission to leave.

\N<Man>Ever since those Ryuda guys started stationing in this town,
the future's been uncertain, but you're safe, right? After
all, Yuia is someone you can rely on.
